cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.CR

The paper deals with the problem of cross-device user matching, which involves learning embeddings from user event sequences. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and cryptography (cs.CR). However, given that the paper focuses on the use of siamese convolutional architectures to learn embeddings, and that it is primarily concerned with improving the state-of-the-art in cross-device user matching, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG.
